{"name":"Gria Heritage - Ocean Wyrm","type":"feat","img":"systems/ffd20/icons/ffxiv_icons/FFXIVIcons-MainCommand%20-%20Others/03_MainCommands/07/character_configuration.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<h1>Variant Gria Heritages</h1><p>Although many grias follow the general model of the gria, many more do not. Those of different lineages may evince dramatically different manifestations of their heritage, both in appearance and in ability. Here are 4 different potential heritages for gria PCs. If you choose to use a specific bloodline instead of the general rules for creating a gria, you should work with your GM to ensure that your character’s appearance reflects that bloodline.</p><h2><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">Ability Score Racial Traits</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">These Gria gain +2 Dexterity, +2 Charisma, and –2 Wisdom.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">Movement</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">Gria have a base speed of 30 feet on land. While gria wings are too small to provide true flight, the same magic that empowers dragons allows gria to achieve limited flight for short periods of time while wearing light or no armor and carrying no more than a light load. A gria can fly with clumsy maneuverability a number of rounds at a time equal to her Constitution bonus. A gria can attempt to fly for longer durations by making Constitution check each additional round of flight (DC 10 + 2 per extra round). A gria’s natural fly speed is equal to her base land speed. After flying, a gria must rest a number of rounds equal to twice the number of rounds spent flying before flying again.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">These Gria have:</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">Loses the ability to fly, but gains a Swim Speed equal to movement speed and the Amphibio</span>us trait, allowing them to breathe both air and water.</p><h2>Description</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">These Gria were born and raised by the ocean, having long forsaken their ability to fly, and instead, using their wings to swim and glide through the water.</span></p>","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"actions":[],"uses":{"per":"","value":0,"maxFormula":""},"attackNotes":[],"effectNotes":[],"changes":[{"_id":"ltiJ0Gip","formula":"2","operator":"add","subTarget":"dex","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"OKI7b66q","formula":"2","operator":"add","subTarget":"cha","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"ZmwjbtcG","formula":"-2","operator":"add","subTarget":"wis","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"pKvel2m1","formula":"30","operator":"add","subTarget":"swimSpeed","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"armorProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":["common","draconic"],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{}},"scriptCalls":[],"subType":"racial","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","disabled":false,"classSkills":{"acr":false,"apr":false,"blf":false,"clm":false,"crf":false,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":false,"dri":false,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":false,"int":false,"kar":false,"kdu":false,"ken":false,"kge":false,"khi":false,"klo":false,"kna":false,"kno":false,"kpl":false,"kre":false,"kte":false,"lin":false,"nav":false,"per":false,"prf":false,"pil":false,"pro":false,"rep":false,"rid":false,"sen":false,"slt":false,"spl":false,"ste":false,"sur":false,"swm":false,"umd":false}},"ownership":{"default":0,"VNk1dF8h7rdEhEd4":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_h6